      >
      or can be purchased at the
      <a href="https://www.scoutshop.org/" target="_blank ">Scout Shop.</a>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-14189">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 1. </span>
      Do the following with your counselor:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14189 mb-requirement-id-14190">
        (a) Explain to your counselor the most likely hazards you may encounter
        during athletics activities, and what you should do to anticipate, help
        prevent, mitigate, and respond to these hazards. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/yC3blqv3kp4?si=TLnyOxBv96ZuyubP"
          target="_blank"
          >Preventing Injuries in Youth Athletes (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14189 mb-requirement-id-14191">
        (b) Show that you know first aid for injuries or illnesses that could
        occur while participating in athletics events, including sprains,
        strains, contusions, abrasions, blisters, dehydration, heat reactions,
        and concussions. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/TZqDBgiEfL8?si=RV6nOMJpa0Rc2LbT"
          target="_blank"
          >Using the RICE Method for Injuries - Rest, Ice, Compress, Elevate
          (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/oGvyiWfXB7c?si=VLL-rINKVqd871yO"
          target="_blank"
          >First Aid Treatment for Wounds (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/OcGeUdfL-s4?si=-4uuzL95rK4Is-T2"
          target="_blank"
          >Top 10 Most Common Sports Injuries (and How to Prevent Them!)
          (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-14192">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 2. </span>
      Do the following with your counselor:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14192 mb-requirement-id-14193">
        (a) Discuss the importance of having a physical examination each year.
        Discuss why overall health, immunizations, medications, allergies, and
        medical history are covered during an examination. Tell your counselor
        when you last underwent a physical examination. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://www.scouting.org/health-and-safety/ahmr/"
          target="_blank"
          >Annual Physical Exam (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14192 mb-requirement-id-14194">
        (b) Explain how you maintain good health habits, especially during
        training, and how the use of tobacco products, alcohol, and other
        harmful substances can negatively affect your health and your
        performance in athletic activities. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/dISDEsTr1Rc?si=4QkQnfQQjYs4GRuf"
          target="_blank"
          >Nutrition Tips for High School Athletes (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/_NUo_52vkkg?si=cy-fCChvsa8SVNQT"
          target="_blank"
          >Refusing Use of Harmful Substances (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14192 mb-requirement-id-14195">
        (c) Describe the elements of a nutritious, balanced diet, and explain
        what you do to maintain a healthy diet. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://www.myplate.gov/eat-healthy/what-is-myplate"
          target="_blank"
          >What is MyPlate? (website)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-14197">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 3. </span>
      Select an athletic activity that interests you, then do the following:
      <br /><i>Resource:</i>
      <a href="https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-28062001" target="_blank"
        >Which Sport Are You Made for? Take Our 60-Second Test (website)</a
      >
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14197 mb-requirement-id-14198">
        (a) With guidance from your counselor, establish a personal training
        program suited to the activity you have chosen. Follow this training
        program for three months. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/oRQEgV0wNtQ?si=5ZjJP2Lq6GboJ8E_"
          target="_blank"
          >Keys to Sport-Specific Training (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14197 mb-requirement-id-14199">
        (b) Use a chart or other tracking method to monitor your progress during
        this time. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://isport360.com/7-powerful-journaling-ideas-for-youth-sports-athletes/%20"
          target="_blank"
          >7 Powerful Journaling Ideas for Youth Sports Athletes (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14197 mb-requirement-id-14200">
        (c) Explain to your counselor the equipment necessary to participate in
        this activity and the appropriate clothing for the activity and the time
        of year. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://www.spookynooksports.com/blog/manheim/equipment-needed-to-play-sports%20"
          target="_blank"
          >Equipment Needed to Play Various Sports (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14197 mb-requirement-id-14201">
        (d) At the end of three months, review your records from requirement
        3(b), and discuss with your counselor what progress you have made during
        training. Tell how your development has affected you mentally and
        physically. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/EHZvmAaXwfk?si=rdzKWbgW6dHqMrRO"
          target="_blank"
          >How Do You Measure Progress? (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-14202">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 4. </span>
      Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14202 mb-requirement-id-14203">
        (a) Explain the rules for two athletic activities, one of which is the
        activity you chose for requirement 3. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://www.rulesofsport.com/%20" target="_blank"
          >Rules of Sports (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14202 mb-requirement-id-14204">
        (b) Discuss the importance of warming up and cooling down before and
        after each training session or event. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/XeEIoGMldyc?si=OXMS8XPru5l5dG7g"
          target="_blank"
          >Stretching and Warming Up (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14202 mb-requirement-id-14205">
        (c) Explain to your counselor what an amateur athlete is and the
        differences between an amateur and a professional athlete. <br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a
          href="https://filestore.scouting.org/filestore/Merit_Badge_ReqandRes/Requirement%20Resources/Athletics/amateur_vs_professional.pdf"
          target="_blank"
          >What Is an Amateur (PDF)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14202 mb-requirement-id-14206">
        (d) Discuss the traits and importance of good sportsmanship. Tell what
        role sportsmanship plays in both individual and group athletic
        activities. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/KoDu2FpU57c?si=UgLWB7uM9iY3FQBj"
          target="_blank"
          >What is Good Sportsmanship? (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/rNcfqOqDbsU?si=2C-x-nzDi7v94t50"
          target="_blank"
          >Olympians' Display of Sportsmanship Fosters Positive Attitudes
          (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/BvheyBiD6Qs?si=ZzEwe2jDYlgrIBaU"
          target="_blank"
          >What Does Sportsmanship Mean to You (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-14207">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 5. </span>
      Complete the activities in FOUR of the following options and show
      improvement over a three-month period:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14207 mb-requirement-id-14208">
        <strong>Option A—Sprinting.</strong> Do ALL of the following: <br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/2twa8CAFPls?si=TFVD802jIvX0kmMW"
          target="_blank"
          >How to Sprint (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14208 mb-requirement-id-14209">
        (1) 100-meter dash
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14208 mb-requirement-id-14210">
        (2) 200-meter dash
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14207 mb-requirement-id-14211">
        <strong>Option B—Long-Distance Running.</strong> Do ALL of the
        following: <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/ZKCwpW-l_wU?si=3L7szs0IGkQdhTYR"
          target="_blank"
          >Improving Your Running Form (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14211 mb-requirement-id-14212">
        (1) 3k run
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14211 mb-requirement-id-14213">
        (2) 5k run
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14207 mb-requirement-id-14214">
        <strong>Option C—Long Jump OR High Jump.</strong> Do ALL of the
        following:
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14214 mb-requirement-id-14215">
        (1) Running long jump OR running high jump (best of three tries)<br /><i
          >Resources:</i
        >
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/PeC29LbR94U?si=XUrZ1NjVmZetRdxl"
          target="_blank"
          >Running Long Jump (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/NLufVXI7HOQ?si=vC_x2Ym1yWiTh_H8"
          target="_blank"
          >Running High Jump (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14214 mb-requirement-id-14216">
        (2) Standing long jump OR standing high jump (best of three tries)
        <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/dVgtvAXeBQw?si=nHxJ6Hm9bjzLS5pF"
          target="_blank"
          >Standing Long Jump (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/Q6mxzUBF1_Q?si=XJFxXuwaOeVRxi9A"
          target="_blank"
          >Standing High Jump (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14207 mb-requirement-id-14217">
        <strong>Option D—Swimming.</strong> Do ALL of the following:
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14217 mb-requirement-id-14218">
        (1) 100-meter swim <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/G-Gy76-tGLE?si=ZApjnanynnuBlUWJ"
          target="_blank"
          >How to Swim Laps (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14217 mb-requirement-id-14219">
        (2) 200-meter swim <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/libZMpLYfEM?si=_nSxrUPF1rA317sr"
          target="_blank"
          >Best Way to Swim a 200m (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14207 mb-requirement-id-14220">
        <strong>Option E—Pull-Ups AND Push-Ups.</strong> Do ALL of the
        following:
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14220 mb-requirement-id-14221">
        (1) Pull-ups in two minutes <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/eSPO3E7Qoy4?si=1gK0noTZ_uAteC2P"
          target="_blank"
          >How to Do a Pull-Up (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14220 mb-requirement-id-14222">
        (2) Push-ups in two minutes <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/x-bWOeFFQvk?si=uR2OS3C6KUvyjuSJ"
          target="_blank"
          >How to Do a Push-Up (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14207 mb-requirement-id-14223">
        <strong>Option F—Baseball Throw.</strong> Do ALL of the following:<br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/UHRU973uu2c?si=eu9KwMfgqkKxrSCK"
          target="_blank"
          >How to Throw a Baseball (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14223 mb-requirement-id-14224">
        (1) Baseball throw for accuracy, 10 throws at a target (distance to be
        determined by age): ages 11 to 12, 20 feet; ages 13 to 15, 30 feet; ages
        16 to 17, 40 feet
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14223 mb-requirement-id-14225">
        (2) Baseball throw for distance, five throws (total distance)
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14207 mb-requirement-id-14226">
        <strong>Option G—Basketball Shooting.</strong> Do ALL the following:
        <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/iW2VFzBiaQo?si=OcW1PTb8DR3ZtR6y"
          target="_blank"
          >How to Shoot a Free Throw (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/q4IqeXob_qg?si=or8nQWc5bXpIOEQe"
          target="_blank"
          >How to Shoot a Layup (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/UcnB9e5O5NY?si=dlC30TAj-AyuKca9"
          target="_blank"
          >How to Shoot a Basketball (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14226 mb-requirement-id-14227">
        (1) Basketball shot for accuracy, 10 free-throw shots
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14226 mb-requirement-id-14228">
        (2) Basketball throw for skill and agility, the following shots:
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14228 mb-requirement-id-14238">
        (a) Left-side layup
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14228 mb-requirement-id-14239">
        (b) Right-side layup
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14228 mb-requirement-id-14240">
        (c) Left side of hoop, along the key line
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14228 mb-requirement-id-14241">
        (d) Right side of hoop, along the key line
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14228 mb-requirement-id-14243">
        (e) Where key line and free-throw line meet, left side
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14228 mb-requirement-id-14242">
        (f) Where key line and free-throw line meet, left side
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14228 mb-requirement-id-14244">
        (g) Top of the key
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14228 mb-requirement-id-14245">
        (h) Another spot along the three-point line
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14207 mb-requirement-id-14229">
        <strong>Option H—Football Kick OR Soccer Kick.</strong> Do ALL of the
        following:
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14229 mb-requirement-id-14230">
        (1) Goals from the 10-yard line, eight kicks <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/ROZXyk98Oto?si=D68RBCQ6GDI2_kP9"
          target="_blank"
          >Shooting a Soccer Free Kick (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14229 mb-requirement-id-14231">
        (2) Football kick or soccer kick for distance, five kicks (total
        distance)<br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/vJ3BHM9U-S0?si=xCzYWo3YkxdOXkfu"
          target="_blank"
          >Kick a Football Field Goal (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14207 mb-requirement-id-14232">
        <strong>Option I—Weight Training.</strong> Do ALL of the following:
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14232 mb-requirement-id-14233">
        (1) Chest/bench press, two sets of 15 repetitions each <br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/bt-yRU4HEZ4?si=Jw0QKVOvUsgcIKGa"
          target="_blank"
          >How to Bench Press (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14232 mb-requirement-id-14234">
        (2) Leg curls, two sets of 15 repetitions each<br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/UAod62tMmhk?si=zXLVoKYT_8HPRbgp"
          target="_blank"
          >How to Do Leg Curls (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-14235">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 6. </span>
      Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14235 mb-requirement-id-14236">
        (a) Prepare plans for conducting a sports meet or field day that
        includes 10 activities, at least five of which must come from the groups
        mentioned in requirement 5. Outline the duties of each official needed
        and list the equipment the meet will require. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/IKYtSzrvCjA?si=rJ1j-hy0TLs4ruVQ"
          target="_blank"
          >Planning a Field Day (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14235 mb-requirement-id-14237">
        (b) With your parent or guardian's and counselor's approval, serve as an
        official or volunteer at a sports meet to observe officials in action.
        Tell your counselor about your responsibilities at the meet and discuss
        what you learned. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/ZVFce0ZtaSk?si=FRBbdo8aHRce49C3"
          target="_blank"
          >How to Serve as a Swim Meet Timer (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/BGW1IZPLuGk?si=A7H469w658jlC_y7"
          target="_blank"
          >Rules of a Swim Meet (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-14246">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 7. </span>
      Do ONE of the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14246 mb-requirement-id-14247">
        (a) Explore three careers related to athletics. Research one career area
        by interviewing an expert in the field, visiting a site, or using other
        resources. Learn about training, education, expenses, job outlook,
        salary, and advancement. Discuss your findings and career interest with
        your counselor. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/ONALKNxTtwI?si=JKi4baFP93-osufW"
          target="_blank"
          >A Career as an Athletic Trainer (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14246 mb-requirement-id-14248">
        (b) Explore how an area of athletics could contribute to a hobby or
        healthy lifestyle. Research education, costs, and organizations related
        to this activity. Discuss your findings and goals with your counselor.
        <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/QnfVwg4HWzg?si=8Sgu-6MwAh0kFjrQ"
          target="_blank"
          >Making Athletics a Habit (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
</div>
